253
00:09:23.496 --> 00:09:25.296
to find your husband.

254
00:09:29.169 --> 00:09:30.999
♪ ♪

255
00:09:33.741 --> 00:09:35.141
It's empty.

256
00:09:35.242 --> 00:09:38.112
Looked in all the windows.
No furniture. nothing.

257
00:09:38.211 --> 00:09:39.911
I could probably pick
the lock in back. but... No.

258
00:09:40.013 --> 00:09:43.783
Todd. no. That's criminal.
Six months minimum.

259
00:09:45.653 --> 00:09:47.223
While you were gone.

260
00:09:47.320 --> 00:09:48.660
I was picturing him
in there.

261
00:09:48.689 --> 00:09:51.089
What if he hung himself
in that garage?

262
00:09:51.191 --> 00:09:54.191
Like Bradley Coopman
in that Madonna movie.

263
00:09:54.294 --> 00:09:55.204
<i>Starborn.</i>

264
00:09:55.295 --> 00:09:58.025
Like Bradley Cooper

265
00:09:58.131 --> 00:10:00.931
in the Lady Gaga movie
<i>A Star Is Born?</i>

266
00:10:01.034 --> 00:10:02.904
And why would he
send his bills

267
00:10:03.003 --> 00:10:06.043
to a house where he's dead?
That doesn't make any sense.

268
00:10:06.139 --> 00:10:07.569
(phone ringing)

269
00:10:07.675 --> 00:10:09.775
It's Allison.
Don't answer that.

270
00:10:09.877 --> 00:10:12.347
I don't want anyone in the
family to know what's going on.

271
00:10:12.445 --> 00:10:13.775
You know
I'm in the family. right?

272
00:10:13.881 --> 00:10:16.021
Hang up. Fine.

273
00:10:16.116 --> 00:10:18.086
So. what do we do now?
(sighs)

274
00:10:18.185 --> 00:10:19.915
Sit here? Waiting?

275
00:10:20.020 --> 00:10:23.290
We have no other leads.
he is linked to this house.

276
00:10:23.390 --> 00:10:25.990
and he has to sleep
somewhere tonight.

277
00:10:27.661 --> 00:10:29.461
(smacks lips)

278
00:10:29.562 --> 00:10:31.102
(smacks lips)

279
00:10:34.167 --> 00:10:36.097
MARGARET:
This is insane.

280
00:10:36.203 --> 00:10:37.243
I mean. this seat

281
00:10:37.337 --> 00:10:39.067
is filthy. (stammers)

282
00:10:39.172 --> 00:10:41.272
What is all this junk
down here at my feet?

283
00:10:41.374 --> 00:10:42.744
Is that a telescope?

284
00:10:42.843 --> 00:10:45.613
It's a lens for
a camera. a long lens.

285
00:10:45.713 --> 00:10:47.183
Todd. without your license.

286
00:10:47.280 --> 00:10:49.150
you are not allowed to work
as a private detective

287
00:10:49.249 --> 00:10:51.049
in the state of...
Yes. I know that.
Thank you very much. Mother.

288
00:10:51.151 --> 00:10:52.851
I am just finding people
and taking photos

289
00:10:52.953 --> 00:10:56.063
for health insurance companies.
okay? Pays the bills.

290
00:10:56.156 --> 00:10:58.326
Almost.
Well. I had hoped

291
00:10:58.425 --> 00:11:00.925
that you would get out
of this field altogether.

292
00:11:01.028 --> 00:11:03.728
considering the amount of
trouble you got yourself into.

293
00:11:03.764 --> 00:11:05.404
Mom. I am a private detective.

294
00:11:05.498 --> 00:11:06.728
You were.
It is all I've

295
00:11:06.800 --> 00:11:08.400
ever wanted to be.

296
00:11:08.501 --> 00:11:10.641
You gave me that copy of <i>Harriet
the Spy</i> when I was nine.

297
00:11:10.738 --> 00:11:12.168
and I am very. very good
at this job.

298
00:11:12.272 --> 00:11:13.812
Well...
And if it weren't for me.

299
00:11:13.907 --> 00:11:15.807
you would still be
in your empty condo alone

300
00:11:15.909 --> 00:11:17.509
with no idea where
your husband is.

301
00:11:17.610 --> 00:11:20.580
As opposed to
where we are.

302
00:11:20.748 --> 00:11:21.878
which is nowhere.

303
00:11:21.982 --> 00:11:24.222
(electric recliner humming)

304
00:11:28.388 --> 00:11:30.758
(owl hooting)

305
00:11:30.858 --> 00:11:33.128
(cat yowling)

306
00:11:33.226 --> 00:11:35.896
TODD:
Who was having a baby
on the phone?

307
00:11:35.996 --> 00:11:37.426
Oh. that's Nadia.

308
00:11:37.530 --> 00:11:40.400
She's the investigator
on my current case. Oh.

309
00:11:40.500 --> 00:11:43.240
You remember my
sorority sister Celia?
No.

310
00:11:43.336 --> 00:11:44.396
And her daughter Kim.

311
00:11:44.504 --> 00:11:46.274
No.
Todd. Kim.

312
00:11:46.373 --> 00:11:47.783
We tried to set you up
with her once.

313
00:11:47.875 --> 00:11:48.775
but she thought you were weird.

314
00:11:48.876 --> 00:11:50.806
She has now
been accused

315
00:11:50.911 --> 00:11:52.911
of murdering her boss.

316
00:11:53.013 --> 00:11:55.453
Oh. Oh. great.
That's nice.

317
00:11:55.548 --> 00:11:56.948
He sexually assaulted her

318
00:11:57.050 --> 00:11:59.190
at the office Christmas party.

319
00:11:59.286 --> 00:12:00.886
Oh.
Anyway.

320
00:12:00.988 --> 00:12:03.558
the boss leaves the party
a few hours later.

321
00:12:03.656 --> 00:12:05.556
goes to the rooftop

322
00:12:05.658 --> 00:12:07.228
of a nearby parking garage.

323
00:12:07.327 --> 00:12:11.057
and is shot to death
sitting in his car.

324
00:12:11.164 --> 00:12:11.934
Oh.

325
00:12:12.032 --> 00:12:14.002
But she didn't do it?

326
00:12:14.101 --> 00:12:16.641
No forensic evidence.
no gunpowder. nothing.

327
00:12:16.804 --> 00:12:19.314
Though she did own a gun once.

328
00:12:19.406 --> 00:12:21.666
Oh.
But she lost it
two years ago when

329
00:12:21.809 --> 00:12:23.039
she moved back in
with her parents.

330
00:12:23.143 --> 00:12:25.583
In any event. we're trying
to nail down witnesses

331
00:12:25.678 --> 00:12:26.908
who saw her on the bus

332
00:12:27.014 --> 00:12:28.924
before the trial resumes
on Monday.

333
00:12:29.016 --> 00:12:30.376
Resumes?
Yes.

334
00:12:30.483 --> 00:12:33.653
The state prosecutor fell
down the stairs in his home

335
00:12:33.821 --> 00:12:35.861
and gave himself
a serious concussion.

336
00:12:35.956 --> 00:12:38.226
So the judge granted them
a two-week continuance.

337
00:12:38.325 --> 00:12:39.825
He has a serious concussion

338
00:12:39.927 --> 00:12:40.957
and he's coming back to work

339
00:12:41.061 --> 00:12:42.301
in two weeks?
Yes.

340
00:12:42.395 --> 00:12:43.555
I've tracked down
a few concussed people.

341
00:12:43.663 --> 00:12:45.003
and if you've really got one.

342
00:12:45.098 --> 00:12:46.928
you're on strict bed rest
for a month. minimum.

343
00:12:47.034 --> 00:12:48.874
So the state prosecutor
is a liar.

344
00:12:48.969 --> 00:12:50.939
What's the name of
this concussion guy?

345
00:12:51.038 --> 00:12:52.838
Christopher Barrett.
Christopher Barrett.

346
00:12:52.940 --> 00:12:54.740
Wait. so you're gonna look him
up on your phone. Wonderful.

347
00:12:54.842 --> 00:12:56.882
Your generation is addicted
to your devices.
Mr. Barrett. Oh.

348
00:12:56.977 --> 00:12:58.647
His daughter...
Try to solve everything
through apps. and...

349
00:12:58.745 --> 00:12:59.945
Who has a TikTok.
of course.

350
00:13:00.047 --> 00:13:02.177
...then beepMo and podcasts.
Uh-huh.

351
00:13:02.282 --> 00:13:04.052
Oh. Oh. yes. There.
Oh. God.

352
00:13:04.151 --> 00:13:05.891
I cannot keep my eyes open.
Oh. hello.

353
00:13:05.986 --> 00:13:07.746
Mr. Serious Concussion Man.
How do you ignore
the odor in this car?

354
00:13:07.855 --> 00:13:09.015
Mom. take a look at this.

355
00:13:09.122 --> 00:13:11.762
What is this?
What is she doing?

356
00:13:11.859 --> 00:13:13.959
Is that Tok-Tok?

357
00:13:15.762 --> 00:13:16.862
Is that him?

358
00:13:16.964 --> 00:13:18.604
That's him exercising.
what's that.

359
00:13:18.698 --> 00:13:20.598
six. seven.
eight days ago?

360
00:13:20.700 --> 00:13:22.040
Looks fine to me.

361
00:13:22.135 --> 00:13:24.095
But then. this is a lie.

362
00:13:24.204 --> 00:13:26.614
If he is not injured.

363
00:13:26.706 --> 00:13:29.176
then they are stalling.

364
00:13:29.276 --> 00:13:31.976
They are waiting for
a piece of evidence

365
00:13:32.079 --> 00:13:34.179
that they don't have.
so that they...

366
00:13:34.281 --> 00:13:36.281
We have to get down
to the courthouse right now.

367
00:13:36.383 --> 00:13:39.193
Start the car. Oh. my God.
it's 2:00 in the morning.

368
00:13:39.286 --> 00:13:40.616
Oh. God. but then
who's gonna stay here

369
00:13:40.720 --> 00:13:41.990
to watch the house
for Harry?

370
00:13:42.089 --> 00:13:43.219
Here. hold this.

371
00:13:43.323 --> 00:13:45.233
These burners could
be our eyes.

372
00:13:45.325 --> 00:13:48.455
Disposable phones. Mom.

373
00:13:57.370 --> 00:13:58.270
TODD:
<i>This place is closed.</i>

374
00:13:58.371 --> 00:13:59.471
MARGARET:
But by law.

375
00:13:59.572 --> 00:14:00.912
the records room
has to be attended

376
00:14:00.974 --> 00:14:02.384
24 hours a day.

377
00:14:02.475 --> 00:14:05.075
and. if you play
your cards right.

378
00:14:05.178 --> 00:14:07.948
you just might get in there.

379
00:14:08.048 --> 00:14:09.618
Damn it.

380
00:14:09.716 --> 00:14:11.746
Okay. you stay here.
I'll go around front.

381
00:14:13.153 --> 00:14:14.323
Can I help you?

382
00:14:14.421 --> 00:14:18.091
Uh. yes.
I am Inspector Clip

383
00:14:18.191 --> 00:14:19.661
with the Portland Gas Company.

384
00:14:19.759 --> 00:14:21.729
and someone has reported a leak
in the records room.

385
00:14:21.828 --> 00:14:24.628
so I just need access to that
so I can check on it.

386
00:14:24.731 --> 00:14:25.931
A gas leak?

387
00:14:26.033 --> 00:14:27.173
Mm-hmm.
MARGARET:
Todd.

388
00:14:27.267 --> 00:14:29.767
What are you doing?

389
00:14:29.937 --> 00:14:32.207
How are you. Jenny dear?
Hi.

390
00:14:32.305 --> 00:14:34.265
The. uh. new guard let me in.
Uh-huh.

391
00:14:34.374 --> 00:14:35.584
Edgar.
Mm-hmm.

392
00:14:35.675 --> 00:14:37.375
Will you please let us
into the records room?

393
00:14:37.477 --> 00:14:38.947
I have a pressing matter.

394
00:14:38.979 --> 00:14:41.709
And this is my son Todd.

395
00:14:42.682 --> 00:14:44.352
Hi.

396
00:14:46.486 --> 00:14:49.056
MARGARET:
I must have spent years
of my life down here

397
00:14:49.156 --> 00:14:50.516
filing and sorting briefs.

398
00:14:50.623 --> 00:14:53.333
Once I passed the bar.
I got my nails done

399
00:14:53.426 --> 00:14:56.096
and swore I'd never break
another one pulling files.

400
00:14:56.196 --> 00:14:57.756
Ah. found it.
Right here.

401
00:14:57.864 --> 00:14:59.304
Okay. bring it.

402
00:14:59.399 --> 00:15:01.069
All right.
so this is my case.

403
00:15:01.168 --> 00:15:03.538
Now. I want you to flip to
the evidence log in the back.

404
00:15:03.636 --> 00:15:05.406
How many pieces of evidence
have been logged and tagged?

405
00:15:05.505 --> 00:15:07.365
It's the back flap.
yes? Red box.

406
00:15:07.474 --> 00:15:08.984
Nine.
Nine. okay. same here.

407
00:15:09.009 --> 00:15:10.309
Maybe not new evidence.

408
00:15:10.410 --> 00:15:13.310
Try the front flap. gray box.
How many witnesses?

409
00:15:13.413 --> 00:15:15.323
Witnesses... 15.

410
00:15:15.415 --> 00:15:16.975
Fifteen or 50?
Fifteen.

411
00:15:17.084 --> 00:15:18.854
One. five. Fifteen. Okay.

412
00:15:18.986 --> 00:15:22.186
13. 14. 15.

413
00:15:22.289 --> 00:15:24.489
Sixteen.

414
00:15:24.591 --> 00:15:26.561
They're introducing
a new witness.

415
00:15:26.659 --> 00:15:28.499
Isn't that something
that happens?
Yes.

416
00:15:28.595 --> 00:15:32.995
But they're required to file
weeks in advance. and inform me.

417
00:15:33.066 --> 00:15:35.666
Witness OA1...

418
00:15:35.768 --> 00:15:39.608
They must have found someone
after the start of the trial.

419
00:15:39.706 --> 00:15:42.236
and they're filing in secret
because they don't want me

420
00:15:42.342 --> 00:15:44.312
to find out and block it.

421
00:15:44.411 --> 00:15:46.181
So. like. someone who
saw her kill him.

422
00:15:46.279 --> 00:15:47.579
She didn't kill him. Todd.

423
00:15:47.680 --> 00:15:49.650
Okay. someone who thinks
they saw her kill him.

424
00:15:49.749 --> 00:15:51.719
Witness OA16.

425
00:15:51.818 --> 00:15:55.558
"Witness in possession of
a Vex800-MP9." What is...

426
00:15:55.655 --> 00:15:58.285
MP9 is a kind of
digital video file.

427
00:15:58.391 --> 00:16:00.661
Like. from a security camera.

428
00:16:00.760 --> 00:16:03.700
So they have a new
witness who has a video

429
00:16:03.796 --> 00:16:05.696
of something bad for you.

430
00:16:05.798 --> 00:16:08.868
Something bad enough
to make them fake an injury

431
00:16:09.036 --> 00:16:09.896
and slow down the case.

432
00:16:10.037 --> 00:16:11.337
Are you sure
she didn't kill him?

433
00:16:11.438 --> 00:16:12.808
(alarm sounding)
(gasps)

434
00:16:12.905 --> 00:16:14.535
Todd... Wait. Todd.
What did you touch?

435
00:16:14.641 --> 00:16:16.341
That's not me. I don't...
Oh. wait. no. that's my phone.

436
00:16:16.443 --> 00:16:18.513
It's the burners.
The cameras that we left.

437
00:16:18.611 --> 00:16:20.651
There's activity
at that house.

438
00:16:20.747 --> 00:16:23.577
(gasps) Who was that?
Was that Harry?

439
00:16:23.683 --> 00:16:25.953
He's locking the door.

440
00:16:26.853 --> 00:16:29.293
What does he have
in his hands?

441
00:16:29.389 --> 00:16:30.589
What is that?
It's a baby.

442
00:16:30.690 --> 00:16:33.060
TODD:
That's not Harry.

443
00:16:33.093 --> 00:16:35.403
Who the hell was that?

444
00:16:39.832 --> 00:16:43.372
Our in-house investigator. Lyle.
who is remarkably precise.

445
00:16:43.470 --> 00:16:44.870
is right down there.

446
00:16:44.971 --> 00:16:47.471
He can get you access
to the RMLS website.

447
00:16:47.574 --> 00:16:49.884
and maybe you can find out
more about...

448
00:16:49.976 --> 00:16:52.346
that house that Harry...

449
00:16:52.445 --> 00:16:53.505
In Gresham.

450
00:16:53.613 --> 00:16:55.253
Mom. it's okay.

451
00:16:55.348 --> 00:16:57.278
I'll find him.
I promise.

452
00:16:57.384 --> 00:17:00.224
No. no. I am fine.

453
00:17:00.320 --> 00:17:01.790
Kim will be here
any minute.

454
00:17:01.888 --> 00:17:04.988
and I do not let my personal
life interfere with my work.

455
00:17:05.092 --> 00:17:06.662
♪ The way I'm slippin' away ♪

456
00:17:06.759 --> 00:17:09.329
♪ I turn my feelings on ♪

457
00:17:09.429 --> 00:17:10.959
♪ You made me untouchable... ♪

458
00:17:11.098 --> 00:17:13.368
Hey. Morning.

459
00:17:13.466 --> 00:17:15.266
Ooh.

460
00:17:15.368 --> 00:17:17.968
♪ And you wasn't polite... ♪

461
00:17:18.105 --> 00:17:19.805
Hey. are you Lyle?

462
00:17:19.906 --> 00:17:22.976
I need access to the RMLS
property info database.

463
00:17:23.110 --> 00:17:24.910
And you are?

464
00:17:25.011 --> 00:17:27.911
Todd. Wright.

465
00:17:28.014 --> 00:17:31.524
My mother Margaret Wright
is a partner here. so

466
00:17:31.618 --> 00:17:34.448
she's basically your boss.
(chuckles)

467
00:17:34.554 --> 00:17:36.224
Your mother is not my boss.

468
00:17:36.323 --> 00:17:37.793
I'm an employee
of the firm.

469
00:17:37.890 --> 00:17:39.860
answering only to the bylaws
of the corporation.

470
00:17:39.959 --> 00:17:41.559
None of us share
investigative database access

471
00:17:41.661 --> 00:17:42.861
with nonemployees.

472
00:17:42.962 --> 00:17:44.902
Okay.
Nor with former investigators

473
00:17:44.997 --> 00:17:47.427
stripped of their licenses
following criminal charges

474
00:17:47.534 --> 00:17:49.474
for illegal wiretapping
and forgery.

475
00:17:49.569 --> 00:17:51.699
I had nothing to do
with the forgery.

476
00:17:51.804 --> 00:17:53.614
Oh. I remember your defense.

477
00:17:53.706 --> 00:17:57.236
You were seduced and deceived
by your mentor.

478
00:17:57.344 --> 00:17:58.414
You thought you were
equal partners

479
00:17:58.511 --> 00:17:59.751
in your little
detective agency.

480
00:17:59.846 --> 00:18:01.806
and you had no idea
she was making you

481
00:18:01.914 --> 00:18:03.754
the fall guy
for her criminal activities.

482
00:18:03.850 --> 00:18:05.890
Yeah. That's right.

483
00:18:05.985 --> 00:18:08.155
Well. your mother could
keep you out of jail.

484
00:18:08.221 --> 00:18:10.191
but she can't force you
in my office.

485
00:18:10.290 --> 00:18:11.820
Good day. Look.

486
00:18:11.924 --> 00:18:13.534
I just need information
about a house.

487
00:18:13.626 --> 00:18:15.156
It's personal.
for my mom.

488
00:18:15.228 --> 00:18:16.758
Personal searches are
strictly forbidden.

489
00:18:16.863 --> 00:18:21.233
And so is eating in my office.
Crumbs. Get out!

490
00:18:23.270 --> 00:18:26.170
(vacuum whining)

491
00:18:26.239 --> 00:18:27.869
(sighs heavily)

492
00:18:27.974 --> 00:18:30.084
(indistinct chatter)

493
00:18:32.179 --> 00:18:35.279
Oh. my God. Todd.

494
00:18:35.382 --> 00:18:37.522
Hi.

495
00:18:37.617 --> 00:18:40.517
Susan. Hi.

496
00:18:40.620 --> 00:18:43.720
You work for my mother?

497
00:18:43.823 --> 00:18:45.533
I work <i>with</i> your mother.

498
00:18:45.625 --> 00:18:47.485
Wow. I haven't seen you
since we...

499
00:18:47.594 --> 00:18:49.034
We? Since you.
I mean. I didn't...

500
00:18:49.196 --> 00:18:50.396
Okay. since I...
I would never.
You were the...

501
00:18:50.497 --> 00:18:51.397
Well. it ended.

502
00:18:51.498 --> 00:18:53.528
I didn't...

503
00:18:53.633 --> 00:18:54.633
You're married.

504
00:18:54.734 --> 00:18:57.204
Oh. engaged. just last month.

505
00:18:57.304 --> 00:18:58.844
Peter.
Peter. Cool.

506
00:18:58.938 --> 00:19:00.938
You know. I have to tell you
that your mom is

507
00:19:01.040 --> 00:19:02.310
such a wonderful woman.

508
00:19:02.409 --> 00:19:04.839
She's so encouraging
and supportive.

509
00:19:04.944 --> 00:19:07.254
Uh. okay.
(door shuts)

510
00:19:07.347 --> 00:19:10.017
Hey. listen.

511
00:19:10.116 --> 00:19:12.246
maybe you'd be willing to do
my mother a little favor.

512
00:19:12.352 --> 00:19:15.892
You see. uh. there's
this house in Gresham...

513
00:19:15.988 --> 00:19:17.558
NIKI:
<i>Kim is my girlfriend.</i>

514
00:19:17.657 --> 00:19:19.127
Her house arrest
should be at my place.

515
00:19:19.226 --> 00:19:20.886
She says you just cry
and he's yelling all day.

516
00:19:20.993 --> 00:19:22.403
Who the hell do you
think you are?

517
00:19:22.495 --> 00:19:23.655
She's my daughter.
damn it.

518
00:19:23.763 --> 00:19:25.473
KIM: Can both
of you please

519
00:19:25.565 --> 00:19:26.495
stop fighting?

520
00:19:26.599 --> 00:19:27.799
Walter. Niki.

521
00:19:27.900 --> 00:19:28.970
go somewhere else. please.

522
00:19:29.068 --> 00:19:30.368
CELIA:
They're just upset.

523
00:19:30.470 --> 00:19:31.940
WALTER:
Just don't say anything.
Come with me.

524
00:19:32.038 --> 00:19:34.468
MARGARET:
Just relax. Kim. relax.

525
00:19:34.574 --> 00:19:35.744
(whispering indistinctly)

526
00:19:35.842 --> 00:19:36.812
MARGARET:
It's all gonna be fine.

527
00:19:36.909 --> 00:19:37.879
I promise you.

528
00:19:37.977 --> 00:19:40.247
Take a deep breath. all right?

529
00:19:44.116 --> 00:19:46.086
(grunts)

530
00:19:51.624 --> 00:19:54.064
Just. uh...

531
00:19:55.528 --> 00:19:57.058
NIKI (over earbud):
I only wanted to protect her.

532
00:19:57.163 --> 00:19:59.533
WALTER (over earbud):
And that is our secret. okay?

533
00:19:59.632 --> 00:20:02.202
If anyone can get her off.
it's this bitch lawyer

534
00:20:02.302 --> 00:20:03.302
that Celia hired.

535
00:20:03.403 --> 00:20:04.203
Just keep it...
(door opens)

536
00:20:04.304 --> 00:20:05.544
Good morning.

537
00:20:05.638 --> 00:20:07.608
I want to thank you all
for coming back in

538
00:20:07.707 --> 00:20:09.677
on such short notice.

539
00:20:09.776 --> 00:20:12.876
I have discovered
that the prosecution

540
00:20:12.979 --> 00:20:14.279
has a new witness.

541
00:20:14.381 --> 00:20:16.051
(over earbud):
And this witness may possess

542
00:20:16.148 --> 00:20:18.918
security camera footage
that incriminates Kim.

543
00:20:19.018 --> 00:20:21.288
Now. Kim. we've been
through this many times.

544
00:20:21.388 --> 00:20:23.988
but when you left the party.
did you go

545
00:20:24.090 --> 00:20:25.430
straight to the bus stop.

546
00:20:25.525 --> 00:20:28.625
or did you go into
or near any buildings?
No.

547
00:20:28.728 --> 00:20:30.958
She was home by 12:30. Mar.

548
00:20:31.063 --> 00:20:32.103
I heard her come in.

549
00:20:32.198 --> 00:20:34.898
Is there any chance
anyone saw you

550
00:20:35.001 --> 00:20:36.241
with a gun that night?

551
00:20:36.336 --> 00:20:38.866
I know you lost your gun...
Two years ago.

552
00:20:38.971 --> 00:20:41.641
(over earbud):
My God. what is going on here?

553
00:20:41.741 --> 00:20:43.841
I am the victim. not him.

554
00:20:43.943 --> 00:20:45.183
Oh. here you are.

555
00:20:45.278 --> 00:20:47.208
Hi.
Hi. I got the info
that you wanted.

556
00:20:47.314 --> 00:20:49.984
That house is a rental owned by
Lodging and Rental Incorporated.

557
00:20:50.082 --> 00:20:52.082
Thank you.
That's their info.

558
00:20:53.453 --> 00:20:54.653
Is it really for your mom?

559
00:20:54.754 --> 00:20:56.424
Yeah.

560
00:20:56.523 --> 00:20:57.493
Mm.
Absolutely.

561
00:20:57.590 --> 00:20:58.890
No. no. I'm helping her...

562
00:20:58.991 --> 00:21:00.431
You just needed me to get
around Lyle. didn't you?

563
00:21:00.527 --> 00:21:03.527
Yeah. just kind of put me in
an awkward position with him.

564
00:21:03.630 --> 00:21:05.570
Well. I'm sorry. I...

565
00:21:05.665 --> 00:21:06.995
I lost my PI license.

566
00:21:07.099 --> 00:21:09.039
and I can't run my own
municipal searches.

567
00:21:10.637 --> 00:21:13.337
But you like to...

568
00:21:13.440 --> 00:21:15.340
Play by the rules. Yeah.
Right. And I'm...

569
00:21:15.442 --> 00:21:17.712
Oh. uh. no. no. no.
don't. don't.

570
00:21:17.810 --> 00:21:19.350
I'm not. uh. that's...
(indistinct voices over earbud)

571
00:21:19.446 --> 00:21:20.946
That's not...
I'm not. um...

572
00:21:21.047 --> 00:21:22.677
Can I just...
I'm sorry.

573
00:21:22.782 --> 00:21:26.922
Thank you. No. No. thank you.
I'm just gonna
go back to... Bye.

574
00:21:27.019 --> 00:21:29.359
Susan. wait.
(sighs)

575
00:21:38.731 --> 00:21:41.031
Hey. Mom. I got the info
on that Gresham house.

576
00:21:41.133 --> 00:21:44.203
(gasps) Oh.
The man we saw. "Tomas."
is the landlord.

577
00:21:44.371 --> 00:21:46.711
He lives down the street.
He's married to Rosa.

578
00:21:46.806 --> 00:21:49.676
and I found her on Instagram
holding their newborn baby.

579
00:21:49.776 --> 00:21:51.236
So he was probably
out for a walk

580
00:21:51.378 --> 00:21:53.208
trying to get the baby
back to sleep. Yeah.

581
00:21:53.380 --> 00:21:54.980
And maybe dropping
off something

582
00:21:55.081 --> 00:21:56.421
for his new tenant. Harry.

583
00:21:56.516 --> 00:21:58.386
Anyway. I just left
a voice mail for Tomas.

584
00:21:58.451 --> 00:22:01.721
And by the way. I noticed
that you have photos

585
00:22:01.821 --> 00:22:04.661
of Allison and Lawrence
on your desk. but none of me.

586
00:22:04.757 --> 00:22:06.057
So thank you.

587
00:22:06.158 --> 00:22:07.758
Todd. those are your
siblings' wedding photos.

588
00:22:07.860 --> 00:22:09.400
Get married and I'll be
glad to include you.
(phone vibrates)

589
00:22:09.462 --> 00:22:10.402
(scoffs)

590
00:22:10.430 --> 00:22:11.660
Allison has called me four times

591
00:22:11.764 --> 00:22:12.904
since I was in my meeting.

592
00:22:12.999 --> 00:22:13.999
I wonder what's going on.

593
00:22:14.100 --> 00:22:16.640
Oh. well. she knows.

594
00:22:16.736 --> 00:22:18.936
I told her about Harry
before you told me

595
00:22:19.038 --> 00:22:20.168
not to tell anybody.

596
00:22:20.272 --> 00:22:22.682
Anyway. she would like
both of us

597
00:22:22.775 --> 00:22:24.535
to come over for dinner tonight.

598
00:22:24.644 --> 00:22:28.014
She invited you
for family dinner?

599
00:22:28.981 --> 00:22:32.521
Oh. hi. Mom.
Chuck. they're here.

600
00:22:32.619 --> 00:22:34.949
Mom. I'm...
I don't even know what to say.
I know.

601
00:22:35.054 --> 00:22:36.894
Come on in.
please. please. please.

602
00:22:36.989 --> 00:22:39.729
Yeah.
Hey. So Harry just disappeared
in the night

603
00:22:39.826 --> 00:22:40.986
to go kill himself?

604
00:22:41.093 --> 00:22:43.863
(harsh whisper):
Chuck. What are you doing?

605
00:22:43.963 --> 00:22:45.133
It was just
a question.

606
00:22:45.231 --> 00:22:46.331
Why would you say that?
Coat. please.

607
00:22:46.433 --> 00:22:47.933
No. I don't need a hug. Um...

608
00:22:48.034 --> 00:22:49.844
Why would you say that? Todd.
would you shut the door. please?

609
00:22:49.936 --> 00:22:51.766
Why are you giving this to me?
Oh. Wait. Actually. no. don't.

610
00:22:51.871 --> 00:22:53.441
Hi. Chet.
Perfect timing. Hey.

611
00:22:53.540 --> 00:22:55.640
I'm just gonna
murder everybody. Oh.

612
00:22:55.742 --> 00:22:57.612
Where's your invisible
husband Lawrence?

613
00:22:57.710 --> 00:22:58.950
Well. he can't make it.

614
00:22:59.045 --> 00:23:01.075
Your brother's
a busy guy.
To be expected.

615
00:23:01.180 --> 00:23:02.450
Your daddy's working?

616
00:23:02.482 --> 00:23:04.552
And this daddy needs a beer.

617
00:23:04.651 --> 00:23:05.851
Okay. I just...

618
00:23:05.952 --> 00:23:07.452
ALLISON:
Todd. shut the door.

619
00:23:07.520 --> 00:23:09.790
I'm holding a human being.

620
00:23:09.889 --> 00:23:11.689
TODD:
<i>You've been having
family dinner without me?</i>

621
00:23:11.791 --> 00:23:12.961
Without Uncle Todd?

622
00:23:13.059 --> 00:23:14.689
Every week?
You dinner? No me?

623
00:23:14.794 --> 00:23:16.664
ALLISON:
Mom. again. Chuck and I
are so sorry

624
00:23:16.763 --> 00:23:19.273
to hear this crazy.
awful news.

625
00:23:19.365 --> 00:23:22.195
And we will do whatever we can
to support you.

626
00:23:22.301 --> 00:23:23.671
Allison. thank you.

627
00:23:23.770 --> 00:23:27.040
Um. it is nice to have
my whole family together

628
00:23:27.139 --> 00:23:28.479
at this time.

629
00:23:28.541 --> 00:23:31.711
Well. almost whole.
Uh. is your brother com...

630
00:23:31.811 --> 00:23:33.181
Chet. is Lawrence coming?

631
00:23:33.279 --> 00:23:35.479
No. Unfortunately. he's still
stuck in Hood River

632
00:23:35.515 --> 00:23:36.945
dealing with the flood.

633
00:23:37.049 --> 00:23:38.949
Oh. of course. of course.

634
00:23:39.051 --> 00:23:41.151
His job is very important.

635
00:23:41.253 --> 00:23:42.963
He is the chief

636
00:23:43.055 --> 00:23:44.885
of staff for
the governor of Oregon.

637
00:23:44.991 --> 00:23:46.331
(Margaret chuckles)

638
00:23:46.493 --> 00:23:48.533
Allison. is this the only
wine that we have?

639
00:23:48.628 --> 00:23:49.958
What about that nice
bottle of cabernet

640
00:23:50.062 --> 00:23:52.202
I bought you
for Chuck's birthday?
Oh. yeah.

641
00:23:52.298 --> 00:23:54.868
I think we still have that.
Oh. and. um.

642
00:23:54.967 --> 00:23:56.297
maybe some nicer napkins.

643
00:23:56.402 --> 00:23:58.872
These ones are so thin.
ALLISON:
Sure. Of course.

644
00:23:58.971 --> 00:24:00.171
Chuck. would you get the wine?

645
00:24:00.272 --> 00:24:02.982
But it's my cabernet.
Chuck. please?

646
00:24:03.075 --> 00:24:05.175
Okay.

647
00:24:05.277 --> 00:24:06.677
Thank you.

648
00:24:06.779 --> 00:24:08.519
And how is Celia's case doing?

649
00:24:08.615 --> 00:24:10.775
I mean her daughter; the one
who thought Todd was weird.

650
00:24:10.883 --> 00:24:12.523
MARGARET:
Oh. Kim.

651
00:24:12.552 --> 00:24:14.822
Well. the prosecution
is playing very dirty.

652
00:24:14.921 --> 00:24:17.261
They are trying to slide
a surprise witness

653
00:24:17.356 --> 00:24:19.526
into the entire...
Niki and the dad.

654
00:24:19.559 --> 00:24:21.059
they have solid alibis. right?

655
00:24:21.160 --> 00:24:22.390
Yes. Todd.

656
00:24:22.529 --> 00:24:24.529
And they are not suspects. Okay.

657
00:24:24.564 --> 00:24:27.274
And what were they?
Their alibis?

658
00:24:27.366 --> 00:24:28.736
What are you so suspicious of?

659
00:24:28.835 --> 00:24:31.935
I just don't trust
this Niki person.

660
00:24:32.038 --> 00:24:33.108
Or the dad.

661
00:24:33.205 --> 00:24:34.635
They were acting
really weird today.

662
00:24:34.741 --> 00:24:36.141
and frankly. I don't like
how they were talking about Mom.

663
00:24:36.242 --> 00:24:37.842
When were they talking
about me?

664
00:24:37.944 --> 00:24:39.214
Well. before the meeting.
they were huddled up

665
00:24:39.311 --> 00:24:41.281
and talking about
protecting Kim

666
00:24:41.380 --> 00:24:42.550
and their secret.

667
00:24:42.582 --> 00:24:44.082
and he called you a...

668
00:24:44.183 --> 00:24:46.053
And how do you know this?

669
00:24:46.152 --> 00:24:49.392
My phone ended up in the...

670
00:24:49.556 --> 00:24:50.916
I heard them. okay?

671
00:24:51.023 --> 00:24:52.293
It was just a little
digital eavesdropping. and...

672
00:24:52.391 --> 00:24:53.561
MARGARET:
You were recording

673
00:24:53.660 --> 00:24:55.060
my clients'
private conversation?

674
00:24:55.161 --> 00:24:56.961
No. I wasn't recording them.
but I should have.

675
00:24:57.063 --> 00:24:58.363
Didn't your business partner...
But it's no big deal.

676
00:24:58.464 --> 00:24:59.734
...go to jail for this?

677
00:24:59.832 --> 00:25:01.632
I was collecting
information for <i>you.</i>

678
00:25:01.734 --> 00:25:03.604
Todd!
I think I'm gonna
take Clem upstairs.

679
00:25:03.703 --> 00:25:05.103
I think we should finish
this in the living room.

680
00:25:05.204 --> 00:25:06.244
How could you be so stupid?

681
00:25:06.338 --> 00:25:07.738
You were spying on...

682
00:25:07.840 --> 00:25:09.980
After everything
I've done for you.
Oh. come on.

683
00:25:10.076 --> 00:25:12.476
I lent you money.
I have defended you in court.

684
00:25:12.579 --> 00:25:14.649
and yet you are hellbent
on destroying yourself.

685
00:25:14.747 --> 00:25:16.777
No. I'm not. What is this.
a German opera?

686
00:25:16.883 --> 00:25:18.453
God. I have been
by your side

687
00:25:18.585 --> 00:25:20.715
for two whole days
while Allison's at work.

688
00:25:20.820 --> 00:25:23.190
And Lawrence isn't even here.
but I am.

689
00:25:23.990 --> 00:25:26.690
I am here for you
in your time of need.

690
00:25:26.793 --> 00:25:28.603
Even though you didn't quite
do the same for me

691
00:25:28.661 --> 00:25:30.461
when Dad died. did you?

692
00:25:31.397 --> 00:25:32.967
Excuse me?

693
00:25:33.065 --> 00:25:34.495
"I don't let my personal life
get in the way of my work."

694
00:25:34.601 --> 00:25:36.601
Yeah. very clear.
Very clear.

695
00:25:36.636 --> 00:25:39.106
Dad dies. suddenly poof. gone.

696
00:25:39.205 --> 00:25:41.105
They're off in college
and I'm at home. alone.

697
00:25:41.207 --> 00:25:43.407
while you're. what.
taking the bar exam.

698
00:25:43.509 --> 00:25:45.209
breaking nails in
the courthouse basement?

699
00:25:45.311 --> 00:25:46.751
And now you're all.
"What's wrong with you?

700
00:25:46.846 --> 00:25:48.916
Why is your life
always a mess?"

701
00:25:49.015 --> 00:25:50.975
I mean. seriously. honestly.
back then.

702
00:25:51.083 --> 00:25:53.523
it was like both
my parents had died.

703
00:25:58.457 --> 00:26:01.027
(door opens. shuts)

704
00:26:04.731 --> 00:26:07.731
It just came out.
(phone chimes)

705
00:26:10.637 --> 00:26:12.237
(Todd mutters indistinctly)

706
00:26:12.338 --> 00:26:14.768
(recording):
Hi. my name is Tomas Garcia.

707
00:26:14.874 --> 00:26:16.684
and I'm returning a call

708
00:26:16.776 --> 00:26:19.146
to Todd Wingo of the FBI.

709
00:26:19.245 --> 00:26:21.505
I really don't want
any trouble.

710
00:26:21.648 --> 00:26:24.348
You asked about Harry McDonald.

711
00:26:24.450 --> 00:26:26.150
but I don't know who that is.

712
00:26:26.252 --> 00:26:29.762
We do have a rental in Gresham.
but our new tenant is not him.

713
00:26:29.856 --> 00:26:31.886
Our new tenant is
actually a magician.

714
00:26:31.991 --> 00:26:34.131
Morris the Magnificent.

715
00:26:34.226 --> 00:26:35.656
A magician?

716
00:26:39.331 --> 00:26:40.531
ALLISON:
<i>So this magician has a shop?</i>

717
00:26:40.667 --> 00:26:41.727
TODD:
<i>Apparently.</i>

718
00:26:41.834 --> 00:26:42.844
Thank you for driving me.

719
00:26:42.935 --> 00:26:44.935
My car just needs
a new engine.

720
00:26:45.037 --> 00:26:46.307
Why are you still
looking for Harry

721
00:26:46.405 --> 00:26:48.305
if you're so mad at Mom?
I'm not looking for her.

722
00:26:48.407 --> 00:26:49.677
I'm looking for me.

723
00:26:49.709 --> 00:26:50.979
I just want to know
where he is

724
00:26:51.077 --> 00:26:52.747
and what the hell
he thinks he's doing.

725
00:26:52.845 --> 00:26:54.145
You never liked him.

726
00:26:54.246 --> 00:26:55.246
Yeah. well. neither did you.

727
00:26:55.347 --> 00:26:56.677
I liked him for Mom.

728
00:26:56.783 --> 00:26:59.523
They were happy. I guess.
I don't know.

729
00:26:59.686 --> 00:27:01.286
Marriage is complicated.

730
00:27:01.387 --> 00:27:02.817
(sighs)

731
00:27:02.922 --> 00:27:04.492
Are you and Chuck okay?

732
00:27:04.590 --> 00:27:05.790
Yeah. Why?

733
00:27:05.892 --> 00:27:07.562
You seemed kind of upset
with him at dinner.

734
00:27:07.694 --> 00:27:09.204
when Mom was
ordering you around.

735
00:27:09.295 --> 00:27:11.425
Chuck is... Chuck.

736
00:27:11.530 --> 00:27:14.170
And it's just easier to
let Mom have her way.

737
00:27:14.266 --> 00:27:15.836
You should have
learned that by now.

738
00:27:15.935 --> 00:27:18.135
Yeah. but once you let her
choose the wine and napkins.

739
00:27:18.237 --> 00:27:19.707
then she's choosing
your career.

740
00:27:19.739 --> 00:27:20.769
your clothes. your house.

741
00:27:20.873 --> 00:27:22.473
I mean. where do you end up?

742
00:27:22.574 --> 00:27:24.814
You end up an ER doctor.

743
00:27:24.911 --> 00:27:27.911
married... to Chuck.

744
00:27:30.783 --> 00:27:32.893
Yeah. well. I'm not
doing this for her.

745
00:27:32.985 --> 00:27:35.315
I'm doing it for me.

746
00:27:36.889 --> 00:27:39.089
Thanks for the ride.

747
00:27:40.459 --> 00:27:42.729
(car pulls away)

748
00:27:48.000 --> 00:27:50.470
"Beloved local magician
Morris the Magnificent

749
00:27:50.569 --> 00:27:52.599
presumed lost at sea."

750
00:27:52.739 --> 00:27:53.639
What?

751
00:27:53.740 --> 00:27:55.640
"Disappeared off cruise ship

752
00:27:55.742 --> 00:27:58.042
after terminal cancer
diagnosis."

753
00:27:58.144 --> 00:28:00.884
So he's declared dead
two months ago.

754
00:28:00.980 --> 00:28:03.750
and now he's renting
a house in Gresham?

755
00:28:03.850 --> 00:28:06.220
That is magic.
(loud thud)

756
00:28:12.925 --> 00:28:15.225
(sighs)

757
