00:38:23.535 --> 00:38:24.865
What?
And while we recognize

1004
00:38:24.970 --> 00:38:26.540
that in the state of Oregon.

1005
00:38:26.638 --> 00:38:29.378
first-degree murder carries
a mandatory life sentence...

1006
00:38:29.475 --> 00:38:30.935
What are you doing?
...I would ask

1007
00:38:31.042 --> 00:38:34.012
that you consider the nature
of my client's assault.

1008
00:38:34.112 --> 00:38:36.552
and perhaps reduce
the prison sentence

1009
00:38:36.648 --> 00:38:38.818
to 50 or 60 years.

1010
00:38:38.917 --> 00:38:39.987
No.

1011
00:38:40.085 --> 00:38:43.815
No. She didn't do it.

1012
00:38:43.922 --> 00:38:46.262
That's not her. Mar.

1013
00:38:46.392 --> 00:38:49.192
I only meant to scare him.

1014
00:38:49.294 --> 00:38:52.504
And then he tried
to take the gun.

1015
00:38:52.598 --> 00:38:53.568
and it just...

1016
00:38:53.665 --> 00:38:57.135
I never thought
they'd blame her.

1017
00:39:01.407 --> 00:39:05.937
I just hoped that
it would save her.

1018
00:39:06.044 --> 00:39:08.814
You didn't mean to kill him.

1019
00:39:10.649 --> 00:39:13.319
I can make a jury
understand that.

1020
00:39:13.419 --> 00:39:15.319
REPORTER (over radio):
And the charges against
Kim Marquette were dropped

1021
00:39:15.421 --> 00:39:17.321
as her mother was
taken into custody...
(slurping)

1022
00:39:17.423 --> 00:39:19.593
...following an emotional
outburst in the courtroom.

1023
00:39:19.691 --> 00:39:21.331
And now. for traffic
and weather.

1024
00:39:21.427 --> 00:39:23.557
Tomorrow looking much
like today.

1025
00:39:23.662 --> 00:39:25.532
and as we head into the next...
(radio switches off)

1026
00:39:30.902 --> 00:39:31.902
You're in jail.

1027
00:39:32.003 --> 00:39:35.943
Worse. Airport jail.

1028
00:39:36.041 --> 00:39:37.441
How'd you get in here?

1029
00:39:37.509 --> 00:39:39.609
You have a good lawyer.
(chuckles)

1030
00:39:39.711 --> 00:39:44.181
So. Niki and the dad.
what was their secret?

1031
00:39:44.282 --> 00:39:47.092
Uh. Kim didn't lose her gun
two years ago.

1032
00:39:47.185 --> 00:39:49.315
They took it.
They hid it from her.

1033
00:39:49.455 --> 00:39:52.215
They were worried
she would harm herself.

1034
00:39:52.323 --> 00:39:54.633
She was struggling
with depression.

1035
00:39:54.726 --> 00:39:56.256
But what they didn't
know was that...

1036
00:39:56.361 --> 00:39:59.471
That the mom knew where
the gun was hidden. Aha.

1037
00:39:59.565 --> 00:40:02.465
And what about witness OA16?
German?

1038
00:40:02.568 --> 00:40:05.498
Italian? Romanian?

1039
00:40:05.604 --> 00:40:07.444
Chinese.

1040
00:40:08.239 --> 00:40:12.509
You are very good
at this job.

1041
00:40:14.446 --> 00:40:16.616
Yeah. I-I know.

1042
00:40:16.715 --> 00:40:18.375
Maybe I should
just let you be

1043
00:40:18.484 --> 00:40:20.524
who you want to be.

1044
00:40:21.920 --> 00:40:23.720
Yeah.

1045
00:40:25.323 --> 00:40:27.363
But there is one thing
I could do for you

1046
00:40:27.459 --> 00:40:29.189
to help you get back
on your feet.

1047
00:40:29.294 --> 00:40:31.864
Uh. help us both. actually.

1048
00:40:31.963 --> 00:40:33.803
If you'll let me.

1049
00:40:35.000 --> 00:40:36.900
(indistinct chatter)

1050
00:40:37.002 --> 00:40:38.542
(exhales sharply)

1051
00:40:38.637 --> 00:40:41.637
It is 1:00 p.m..
and it's gonna be fine.

1052
00:40:41.740 --> 00:40:44.510
You're a detective again.
an investigator.

1053
00:40:44.610 --> 00:40:46.140
This is what you want.
(elevator bell dings)

1054
00:40:46.244 --> 00:40:48.114
This is the way back.

1055
00:40:48.213 --> 00:40:49.453
Okay? Right.

1056
00:40:49.548 --> 00:40:52.078
Right? Okay.
Todd?

1057
00:40:52.183 --> 00:40:54.093
Susan.
Congratulations.

1058
00:40:54.185 --> 00:40:56.045
I heard you were
coming aboard.

1059
00:40:56.154 --> 00:40:57.294
Thanks.
Thank you. Yeah.

1060
00:40:57.388 --> 00:40:58.558
Well. it's not
a permanent thing.

1061
00:40:58.657 --> 00:40:59.827
I'm just covering
for the investigator

1062
00:40:59.925 --> 00:41:00.985
on maternity leave.

1063
00:41:01.092 --> 00:41:02.262
Right. Nadia.

1064
00:41:02.360 --> 00:41:03.700
She had twins.
Yeah. yeah.

1065
00:41:03.795 --> 00:41:06.255
And I'll be around now.
so. you know.

1066
00:41:06.364 --> 00:41:08.234
if maybe a lunch happens...

1067
00:41:08.333 --> 00:41:10.443
I mean. we'll be
working together.

1068
00:41:10.536 --> 00:41:12.736
and you'll need me.

1069
00:41:12.838 --> 00:41:14.038
Professionally.

1070
00:41:14.139 --> 00:41:16.439
Okay. yeah.
That sounds great.

1071
00:41:16.542 --> 00:41:19.552
You know. actually. I have
to get to a Zoom. but...

1072
00:41:19.578 --> 00:41:21.608
I'll see you around.

1073
00:41:21.713 --> 00:41:24.153
Yeah.

1074
00:41:24.249 --> 00:41:26.749
♪ ♪

1075
00:41:30.556 --> 00:41:32.756
(indistinct chatter)

1076
00:41:36.027 --> 00:41:38.627
♪ Gotta live it up ♪

1077
00:41:38.730 --> 00:41:41.400
♪ Gotta be strong ♪

1078
00:41:41.567 --> 00:41:42.427
♪ I'm getting on. getting on ♪

1079
00:41:42.568 --> 00:41:43.428
♪ Getting on... ♪

1080
00:41:43.569 --> 00:41:45.669
WOMAN:
Good. right?

1081
00:41:45.771 --> 00:41:48.071
(laughter)

1082
00:41:48.173 --> 00:41:50.843
(knock on door)
TODD: Hello?

1083
00:41:52.578 --> 00:41:55.178
You look so handsome.
You look like an accountant.

1084
00:41:55.280 --> 00:41:57.650
Thank you. Thank you.

1085
00:41:57.749 --> 00:42:00.949
Wait. are you guys going
out to lunch without me?

1086
00:42:01.052 --> 00:42:03.322
You have far too many
cases to catch up on.

1087
00:42:03.421 --> 00:42:05.161
Now. the ties. the socks.

1088
00:42:05.256 --> 00:42:06.586
shirt and belt in that bag

1089
00:42:06.692 --> 00:42:08.592
are more professional
than what you're wearing.

1090
00:42:08.627 --> 00:42:10.597
We can take it out
of your first paycheck.

1091
00:42:10.696 --> 00:42:12.296
And this is your bus pass.

1092
00:42:12.397 --> 00:42:15.597
because you are not driving
that jalopy into this building.

1093
00:42:15.667 --> 00:42:17.467
Okay? See you soon.

1094
00:42:17.603 --> 00:42:19.143
Good luck.

1095
00:42:19.237 --> 00:42:21.337
♪ I'm coming up ♪

1096
00:42:21.439 --> 00:42:23.409
♪ Get on. get up and ♪

1097
00:42:23.508 --> 00:42:25.638
♪ I'm coming up ♪

1098
00:42:26.645 --> 00:42:27.605
♪ Getting on ♪

1099
00:42:27.713 --> 00:42:29.923
♪ Getting. getting ♪

1100
00:42:30.015 --> 00:42:32.145
♪ Oh. get on. get up and ♪

1101
00:42:32.250 --> 00:42:34.750
♪ Getting ♪

1102
00:42:34.853 --> 00:42:36.663
♪ Get on. get up and... ♪

1103
00:42:36.755 --> 00:42:38.385
I will wear the shirt.

1104
00:42:38.489 --> 00:42:41.159
I will wear the tie.

1105
00:42:41.259 --> 00:42:44.999
but I will not take the bus.

